#: ../../../reference/c-api/config.rst:2
msgid "System configuration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/config.rst:6
msgid ""
"When NumPy is built, information about system configuration is recorded, and "
"is made available for extension modules using NumPy's C API.  These are "
"mostly defined in ``numpyconfig.h`` (included in ``ndarrayobject.h``). The "
"public symbols are prefixed by ``NPY_*``. NumPy also offers some functions "
"for querying information about the platform in use."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/c-api/config.rst:13
msgid ""
"For private use, NumPy also constructs a ``config.h`` in the NumPy include "
"directory, which is not exported by NumPy (that is a python extension which "
"use the numpy C API will not see those symbols), to avoid namespace "
"pollution."
msgstr ""

